## Tools and Technologies Used

The Credit Card Approval Prediction project was developed using Python and several powerful libraries and tools for data analysis, machine learning, visualization, and deployment.

| Tool/Library       | Purpose                                                            | Official Link                      |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| Anaconda Navigator | Package management and environment setup for data science projects | https://www.anaconda.com/download  |
| PyCharm            | Python IDE for development, debugging, and project management      | https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/ |
| NumPy              | Numerical computing and array operations                           | https://numpy.org/doc/stable/      |
| Pandas             | Data manipulation and analysis                                     | https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/    |
| Scikit-learn       | Machine learning algorithms and model evaluation                   | https://scikit-learn.org/stable/   |
| Matplotlib         | Data visualization and plotting                                    | https://matplotlib.org/stable/     |
| Seaborn            | Statistical data visualization                                     | https://seaborn.pydata.org/        |
| Flask              | Web framework for deploying machine learning applications          | https://flask.palletsprojects.com/ |

### Installation

Install the required dependencies using:

```bash
pip install numpy pandas scikit-learn matplotlib seaborn flask
```

### Development Environment

Recommended software for running this project:

* Anaconda Navigator
* PyCharm IDE or Jupyter Notebook
* Python 3.x

These tools and libraries provide the necessary environment for data preprocessing, model training, visualization, and deployment of the Credit Card Approval Prediction system.

